<SLUG> BC-NY-HIP-NYT </SLUG>
  
 (ATTN: Fla.)  
 FLORIDA REBUFFS HIP's PROPOSAL TO RAISE FUNDS 
By CHRISTOPHER DREW   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Regulators in Florida Friday rejected a proposal to
let a troubled subsidiary of the Health Insurance Plan of Greater
New York gradually make up a $4.8 million shortfall in its
financial reserves. The Florida Department of Insurance instead
gave the subsidiary, HIP Health Plan of Florida, until Aug. 15 to
restore the reserve to the legally required level, by either lining
up an investor willing to pump cash into the operation or securing
a joint venture with another health care company.
</P>
<P>
   The Florida company has drained tens of millions of dollars from
HIP's New York operation, which is also in financial trouble. The
regulatory action in Florida adds to the pressure on HIP, a
nonprofit health maintenance organization set up to insure New York
City employees and the poor.
</P>
<P>
   Both the New York State Insurance Department and attorney
general's office are investigating allegations of wasteful spending
at HIP. The company was also hurt last year by the collapse of its
operation in New Jersey.
</P>
<P>
   In Florida, the regulators placed HIP's subsidiary under special
supervision On July 19 out of concern that its reserves had fallen
too low to cushion against unexpectedly large medical claims.
</P>
<P>
   Company officials then filed a proposal to eliminate the $4.8
million deficit over eight months by laying off 41 workers, cutting
other costs and raising insurance premiums.
</P>
<P>
   But in a letter Friday, Susanne K. Murphy, the deputy Florida
insurance commissioner, told HIP officials that their plan would
take too long.
</P>
<P>
   David Abernethy, the executive director of the HIP subsidiary,
said he was disappointed that the plan was rejected. He said
company officials were also negotiating with another health care
company that might want to form a joint venture.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-29-00 0105EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
