<P>
   KAN-SCHOOLS-ELECT (Undated) _ It is just a Kansas school board
election, a primary election at that. But no one in Kansas or
anywhere else is taking this race for granted. Tens of thousands of
dollars has been raised, some of it from out of state. Democrats
are switching their party affiliation just to vote for school board
candidates in the Republican primary. And in what political
observers consider extraordinary, Kansas' highest-ranking
Republicans _ the governor and a senator _ have not only weighed in
on the race, but have endorsed opposing candidates in their own
party. By Pam Belluck. 1,500 words.
</P>
