vegetarians. In the process, she has spawned a virtual industry of
Web sites devoted to mocking, reviling or simply haranguing her _
often with the same blunt mean-spiritedness they complain of
regarding the good doctor.
</P>
<P>
   Herewith a sampling of online commentary.
</P>
<P>
   _ By THOMAS VINCIGUERRA
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE) Recently, after nude photos of Dr. Laura
circulated on the Internet, one viewer wrote: (END ITALICS HERE)
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not so much interested in what she looks like. I just want
to see that she just might be a human being after all.''
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN ITALICS HERE) In ``How Could You Do That?! The Abdication
of Character, Courage, and Conscience'' (HarperCollins, 1996), Dr.
Laura writes: ``Acknowledging that you are basically the
perpetrator of your mess of a life is admittedly very upsetting.''
