<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, July 30, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Gerri Hoppe at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   PARAMEDIC-STRESS (Los Angeles) _ Forced to work enormous amounts
of overtime, nearly 40 percent of Los Angeles city paramedics
suffer from post-traumatic stress, according to a new city study.
The Fire Department's medical director and the agency's
psychologist say the results are disturbint, yet the department is
so strapped for cash that officials have not pulled any paramedics
out of duty. By Jordan Smith. (Will move in the ``a'' national and
``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   SOUTHLAND-VINTNERY (Los Angeles) _ How about a nice Topanga
merlot? For the first time since Prohibition, Los Angeles County
will allow winemaking outside of industrial areas. Already,
vineyards in Topanga, Malibu and the Santa Monica Mountains are
gearing up to make the red stuff. By Troy Anderson. (Will move in
the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.
</P>
<P>
   LAUSD-HQ (Los Angeles) _ In their desperate search for downtown
space to build new schools, Los Angeles Unified School District
officials have decided to look in their own back yard, targeting
district headquarters as the site for a new, 1,500-student high
school. By Harrison Sheppard. (Will move in the ``n'' California
news file.)
</P>
