   GOP-TV _ As Republicans prepare to open the convention that will
nominate George W. Bush for president, the networks are putting the
finishing touches on their high-tech skyboxes. Above the convention
floor, the temporary homes for Peter Jennings, Dan Rather, Tom
Brokaw and the rest hover above expected hordes. But with the
exception of a few hours, the skyboxes for ABC, CBS and NBC will be
dark and empty. The PBS and cable news headquarters, however, will
be abuzz. (Holloway, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED Friday.
