   Saint-Exupery. Translated by Richard Howard. (Harcourt,
</P>
<P>
   $18.) A poet's new English rendering of the French
</P>
<P>
   classic. (All ages)
</P>
<P>
   THE BAD BEGINNING, by Lemony Snicket. (HarperCollins, ... 12
....... 3
</P>
<P>
   $8.95.) The three Baudelaire siblings find misfortune
</P>
<P>
   everywhere they turn. (Ages 10 and up)
</P>
<P>
   JOSEPH HAD A LITTLE OVERCOAT, written and illustrated .. 13
...... 3
</P>
<P>
   by Simms Taback. (Viking, $15.99.) A man transforms his
</P>
<P>
   worn-out coat into smaller garments. (Ages 5 to 9)
</P>
<P>
   HENRY HIKES TO FITCHBURG, written and illustrated by ..... 14
....... 3
</P>
<P>
   D.B. Johnson. (Houghton Mifflin, $15.) A tale (inspired
</P>
<P>
   by Thoreau) of two friends and the different routes
</P>
<P>
   they take to reach their destination. (Ages 4 to 8)
